               <p>ARTHUR ASHTON. I lost a handkerchief on the 18th of August while I was in the <placeName id="t18280911-303-crimeloc1557">Court of Chancery</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-303-crimeloc1557" type="placeName" value="Court of Chancery"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-303-crimeloc1557" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-303-off1555 t18280911-303-crimeloc1557"></join>; I did not feel it go - it was taken from my left-hand coat pocket; I missed it when I left for it; I saw it again in the robingroom.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. How long had you used it before? A. Perhaps about half an hour.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-303-person1668">
                  JAMES 
                  BAKER
               <interp inst="t18280911-303-person1668" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
